FIG. 7 is a perspective view of a different mechanism which can used to form the tie cut-out regions;


FIG. 8 is a side sectional view of the tie cutting mechanism of FIG. 7;


FIG. 9 is a perspective view showing the tie cutting mechanism of FIGS. 7 and 8 in its operating position relative to a moving web; and


FIG. 10 is a perspective view of a water jet cutting device which can be used to form the tie cut-out regions.
